6 An Act relating to ad valorem tax; amending 68 O.S.
2021, Sections 2808 and 2847, which relate to
7 definitions and assessments of railroad, air carrier,
and public service corporation property; defining
8 term; requiring the State Board of Equalization to
assess certain property at a certain ratio; updating
9 statutory language; and providing an effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 2808, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 2808. A. As used in the Ad Valorem Tax Code:
16 1. “Public service corporation” means all transportation
17 companies, transmission companies, all gas, electric, light, heat,
18 and power companies, and all waterworks and water power companies,
19 and all persons authorized to exercise the right of eminent domain
20 or to use or occupy any right-of-way, street, alley, or public
21 highway, along, over, or under the same in a manner not permitted to
22 the general public;
23 2. “Transportation company” means any company, corporation,
24 trustee, receiver, or any other person owning, leasing, or operating
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1122 Page 1

1 for hire, a street railway, canal, steamboat line, and also any
2 sleeping car company, parlor car company, and express company, and
3 any other company, trustee, or person in any way engaged in such
4 business as a common carrier. As used in the Ad Valorem Tax Code,
5 the term “transportation company” transportation company shall not
6 include any railroad or any air carrier. However, all railroad and
7 air carrier property shall continue to be valued and assessed by the
8 State Board of Equalization for purposes of ad valorem taxation;
9 3. “Transmission company” means any company, corporation,
10 trustee, receiver, or other person owning, leasing, or operating for
11 hire any telegraph or telephone line or radio broadcasting system;
12 4. “Person” means individuals, partnerships, associations, and
13 corporations in the singular as well as plural number;
14 5. “Video services provider” means a subclass of public service
15 corporations consisting of any public service corporation offering
16 video programming services;
17 6. “Video programming” shall have the same meaning as set forth
18 in 47 U.S.C., Section 522(20); and
19 7. “Fixed wireless broadband Internet service provider” means
20 an entity that solely offers access to the Internet through a
21 stationary fixed point-to-point connection often requiring direct
22 line of sight between the provider’s wireless transmitter and its
23 end-user consumer’s receiver; and
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1122 Page 2

1 8. “Broadband service providers” means a subclass of public
2 service corporations consisting of any company, corporation,
3 trustee, receiver, or other person offering broadband-based services
4 including fixed or mobile Internet access, Voice over Internet
5 Protocol, or Internet protocol television, to end-user consumers.
6 B. As used in the Ad Valorem Tax Code, “transmission company”
7 transmission company and “public service corporation” public service
8 corporation shall not be construed to include cable television
9 companies or fixed wireless broadband Internet service providers.
10 C. Any real or personal property used by any company,
11 corporation, trustee, receiver, or other person owning, leasing, or
12 operating for hire any pipeline or oil or gas gathering system which
13 was assessed by the State Board of Equalization after January 1,
14 1997, shall continue to be assessed by the State Board of
15 Equalization through ad valorem tax year 1998.
16 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 2847, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 2847. A. The property of all railroads, air carriers,
19 and public service corporations shall be assessed annually by the
20 State Board of Equalization at its fair cash value estimated at the
21 price it would bring at a fair voluntary sale.
22 B. Taxable values of real and personal property of all
23 railroads, air carriers, and public service corporations shall be
24 established in accordance with the requirements of Section 8 of
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1122 Page 3

1 Arti cle X of the Oklahoma Constitution. The State Board of
2 Equalization shall determine the taxable value of all taxable
3 property that the Board is required by law to assess and value, and
4 shall determine such taxable value in accordance with the
5 requirements of Section 8 of Article X of the Oklahoma Constitution.
6 C. The State Board of Equalization shall assess the property of
7 that subclass of public service corporations known as video services
8 providers, as defined in Section 2808 of this title, as provided:
9 1. Every video services provider shall file with the State
10 Board of Equalization a certification regarding total gross receipts
11 for the immediate preceding calendar year by April 15 and shall
12 specify the total gross receipts derived from video programming
13 services;
14 2. The State Board of Equalization shall determine the
15 percentage of gross receipts the video services provider has derived
16 from video programming in the immediately preceding calendar year;
17 and
18 3. The percentage determined pursuant to paragraph 2 of this
19 subsection shall be applied to the taxable fair cash value allocated
20 to Oklahoma this state, and the resulting fair cash value
21 attributable to video programming services shall be assessed using
22 the statewide average of the assessment ratios applied to the assets
23 of cable television companies in that tax year. Unless the taxpayer
24 or the State Board of Equalization demonstrates otherwise, the
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1122 Page 4

1 stat ewide average assessment ratio applied to the personal property
2 of a cable television company shall be assumed to be twelve percent
3 (12%).
4 D. The Except as provided for in subsection E of this section,
5 the percentage of fair cash value for real and personal property of
6 railroads, air carriers, and public service corporations required by
7 the Oklahoma Constitution to be taxable shall be the percentage at
8 which it was assessed on January 1, 1996, in accordance with the
9 provisions of paragraph 3 of subsection A of Section 8 of Article X
10 of the Oklahoma Constitution, and, subject to the requirements of
11 federal law, shall be uniformly applied to calculate the taxable
12 values of public service corporation property within the state for
13 the applicable assessment year.
14 E. The State Board of Equalization shall assess the property of
15 that subclass of public service corporations known as broadband
16 service providers, as defined in Section 2808 of this title, at
17 fifteen (15%) of its fair cash value.
18 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective January 1, 2027.
